I'm becoming a DAOC cynic more and more everyday.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utandaina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tandaina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/28/01 9:08:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What happened to fear spells?  Camping?</span><hr size=1> I swear some people WANT to be cynics!  ;)<br>
<br>
No, there are no fear spells in DAoC.   I havn't really missed them to be honest.<br>
<br>
As for named, they are usualy for quests.  Sometimes not, sometimes they are just for flavor.  No they don't have drops like in EQ.  Dungeons have the best loot.  It is totally random.  Why do they ahve better loot than outdoors? Well cause its more dangerous!   You are STILL better off not &quot;camping&quot; a dungeon.  You are much better off moving through it, always moving.<br>
<br>
You can still get good magic drops outside.   They are more rare yes, but its also a whole lot easier killing and stying alive out there.  I've gotten a number of random dropsout in the middle of no where.  They are often very nice.  At least as nice or better than what I'd get in a dungeon at the same level.  But it seems to be totally random. You can NOT camp stuff in the EQ way of it.<br>
<br>
&quot;Itemizing&quot; was in refernce to a dungeon in Albion (the one under Stonehenge I THINK) that was just dropping coin.)  To get the game out on time some things had to slide a bit.  Now they've had time to do the little fiddly bits and this dungeon now has a list of items that will drop there.  They are level 35-50.  Its a level 35-50 dungeon so that SORTA makes sense to me. Yes?  <br>
