<br>
&quot;No, there are no fear spells in DAoC. I havn't really missed them to be honest.&quot;<br>
<br>
I was just curious since every other spell EQ has is in DAOC, so why not fear?  Fear was a very mainstream type spell, and is a spell in most fantasy type games.  Wasnt complaining about this btw, was just curious why a pretty mainstream spell wasnt put in.<br>
--------<br>
<br>
&quot;As for named, they are usualy for quests. Sometimes not, sometimes they are just for flavor. No they don't have drops like in EQ. Dungeons have the best loot. It is totally random. Why do they ahve better loot than outdoors? Well cause its more dangerous! You are STILL better off not &quot;camping&quot; a dungeon. You are much better off moving through it, always moving.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
I'm not sure what dungeons you've done.  Maybe higher lvl ones are like what your saying, but i spent everyday in Tomb of Mithra between lvl 10-14 or so.  There IS camping, and nobody was better off moving through them.  In fact the ones that kept moving were the ones that got wiped out.  You'd be surprised how many things were down a hall that you couldnt see, and how much stuff would just jump on you if you were to just keep moving.  Also, the difficulty of monster gets more difficult as you move deeper, so there really is no point for a group of a particular lvl to move through a dungeon.  Either they'd start out by fighting cons that are good for them then move into stuff more difficult that they couldnt take anyways, or they'd just skip the cons that are gray to them and camp down where they are blue or higher.  I know in theory Mythic was supposed to design dungeons to prevent camping, but all i've seen are people camping areas and in most cases using Mythics policy of 'there isnt supposed to be camping' to fight other people for mobs which basically just turns into a free-for-all.  Anybody that has hit the lowest lvl of Mithra Tomb where the named stuff spawns should know what i mean.  In regards to named, i've received a few magic stuff from them, but i havent killed enough to really see if they do drop special loot(well, they did drop useless special loot as far as i know like mortar and pestle and stuff like that).  What makes me wonder though is everybody is fighting over a named when it spawns.  <br>
------------<br>
&quot;You can still get good magic drops outside. They are more rare yes, but its also a whole lot easier killing and stying alive out there. I've gotten a number of random dropsout in the middle of no where. They are often very nice. At least as nice or better than what I'd get in a dungeon at the same level. But it seems to be totally random. You can NOT camp stuff in the EQ way of it.&quot;<br>
<br>
As far as dungeons 'are supposed to have much more loot because they are dangerous' i can agree with.  However, the problem with that is it crowds a dungeon, as if their not small enough to begin with anyways, and the fact that the drop rate outside is very rare.  I've received drops outside as well, but comparing the drop rate of magic items outside to in a dungeon isnt even comparable.  A dungeons magic item drop rate is way, way higher.  In anycase, regardless of difficulty, all Mythic is doing by focusing magic items in dungeons is making them VERY crowded with tons of  competetion, i.e. fighting for spawns and camp spots.  Has anybody else experienced this?  It cant just be my server(Pellinor) :P   <br>
--------------------.    <br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Itemizing&quot; was in refernce to a dungeon in Albion (the one under Stonehenge I THINK) that was just dropping coin.) To get the game out on time some things had to slide a bit. Now they've had time to do the little fiddly bits and this dungeon now has a list of items that will drop there. They are level 35-50. Its a level 35-50 dungeon so that SORTA makes sense to me. Yes? <br>
<br>
<br>
I see.  I wasnt sure what they meant exactly by itemizing it.  So they just put magic item drops in, thought they might mean by putting out some list of what drops where or something like sites like Allakhazams or Stratics has.<br>
------------<br>
<br>
For the record, i dont try and become a cynic on purpose.  In fact i try and like a game.  I liked UO and i liked EQ, and at least it took me 3 years and 1 year to get jaded on those.  I didnt like AO, and i'm starting to become less enamoured with DAOC.  The hype is way over-exaggerated imo, since i see how wonderful and perfect a game DAOC is in alot of places(even on UO boards).  I just like to tell it like it is, and although people WANT to believe DAOC is the greatest game, its far from it imo.   I find the gameplay more redundant than almost any other mmorpg i've played so far.   I force myself to log in these days just so i can advance further in my lvling treadmill with basically no end in sight since RvR is all about lvl.  Not much to do other than that.  Granted, the game is new and some would say AO is still new.  Those arent excuses imo for saying how great and wonderful a game is when it currently isnt.  Maybe its just me though, but i'd advice anybody that hasnt played DAOC and reading all the hype about it, dont believe alot of it.<br>
