<br>
For one, there's no mind confusion spell in Everquest, and that's far more useful than fear.  Also while many of the spells have a similar function (both games just have subsets of the AD&D spell list, after all), they operate differently enough that you wouldn't use them in the same way.  For example, both the crippling spells in DAOC and the root spells in Everquest are designed to hold a target in place (or nearly so), but in DAOC you can't "root and DoT" or "root and nuke" as in Everquest, and in Everquest you don't have fixed durations as in DAOC.<br>
<br>
<b><i>Whats wrong with kiting anyways? It takes more skill than the way every class currently solo's.</b></i><br>
<br>
The developers were obviously obsessed with preventing kiting, as there are about five redundant safeguards in the game to prevent you from using a speed advantage to kill unusually hard NPCs.  I saw a post by someone at Mythic stating that they had to prevent kiting because it could unbalance the game moreso than in Everquest due to the extremely low downtime in DAOC.<br>
<br>
<b><i>And i'm sorry to you people who cant stand a bad opinion on DAOC but i really dont think its nearly as great as some of you make it out to be, especially in comparison to EQ. As of right now, only the graphics are better, EQ has way more depth, and more options of what you can do when your bored.</b></i><br>
<br>
Everquest has more depth?  ROFL.  Care to cite specific examples for gameplay at your level, even given the current state of DAOC to the matured state of Everquest?<br>
<br>
<b><i>It is possible because my whole goal is to lvl, lvl, lvl, and if i dont want to lvl there isnt anything else to do. I'm not looking forward to anything but just seeing the bar move.</b></i><br>
<br>
Well then maybe the problem isn't the game, it's you.  You can do trade skills, you can do quests, you can enter realm combat -- you have at least as many options as EQ offers.<br>
<br>
I also suggest getting out and grouping.  Unlike Everquest, grouping is almost always more efficient experience-wise, and you can group with just about anyone without worrying about a "necessary" class.<br>
<br>
<b><i>I know some people resent the equipment customizing of EQ, but i miss it. In fact, going for equipment was a nice option other than lvling.  Its pointless for the most part in DAOC.</b></i><br>
<br>
Why is going for equipment "pointless" in DAOC?  How is it more meaningful in Everquest?<br>
<br>
<b><i>Even quests are more detailed in EQ than DAOC.</b></i><br>
<br>
Umm what?  Even looking at Everquest most favorably and DAOC least favorably, they're about comparable.  Have you started your epic quest?<br>
<br>
<b><i>Every one of us goes through the lvling treadmill, and after so much of it, your not looking forward to it.</b></i><br>
<br>
I agree with you there.  I don't like level-based MMRPGS either; that's one of the reasons I'm eagerly anticipating Star Wars Galaxies.  However, I don't see how this makes DAOC worse than Everquest, since they're both leveling games.<br>
<br>
<b><i>I probably am because i think alot of games do get very boring especially when they dont have much depth to them.</b></i><br>
<br>
Depth is really a double-edged sword.  A deep game offers more possibilities, yet it also requires more effort to learn and adjust.  No MMRPG is like Max Payne, where you read a bit about the controls and get right into wasting enemies.  If you're looking for immediate satisfaction, don't play a MMRPG.<br>
<br>
<b><i>but if i reccomended a game to somebody that had never played EQ or DAOC, i would reccomend EQ</b></i><br>
<br>
Be sure to recommend a good book along with it.  <img src=http://www.geocities.com/lag999/rolleyes.txt> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A> at: 11/29/01 12:08:32 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umacnat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Macnat</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://hem1.passagen.se/lonnelid/english.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/29/01 2:44:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .......</span><hr size=1> &gt;&gt;&gt;  I could've sworn Mythic wasnt going to do that so camping wouldnt be a problem. &lt;&lt;&lt;<br>
