Goldmund- Sorry, but i play a Theurg (.  I agree that alot of my problems have to do with it being so new, i'm also judging it now tho.  Hehe, i dunno about your recommended lvls for Mithra, whew.  A lvl 6-7 in there might get torn up, but if he sticks near the entrance with a group then he should be ok.  Just so you know tho, the bottom lvl where the named centurion skeletons spawn(Annilus and others), everything in that room is blue or higher at lvl 15, and sometimes the named are orange.  The bad thing is the hall mobs right outside that room(where i used to solo when the room was taken) greened out when i turned 15, and the room was always taken, so i took off abit after the beginning of 15.  Also, you shouldnt be soloing down there unless your at least lvl 12 imo, but it depends on yoru class i guess.  You can solo in other areas much earlier tho.  <br>
