Nyssa- Well, to be honest i dunno how the lvling treadmill can really be that enjoyable everytime you log on.  For example in EQ, most of us hit that treadmill pretty often to hit lvl 50.  Not even pretty often, but way too often, and its just hard for me to believe that CAN be enjoyable each and everytime you log on.  I mean it had its moments where i was immersed, but after so much of it, it becomes more of a goal than just fun.  The first couple times i killed Cobalt Drakes was fun, but after so many times it became a chore just for exp.  I realize that mmorpg's do require some work(not fun), but like i stated, when i burn out i enjoy doing other things that DAOC just doesnt offer right now.  <br>
<br>
Just so you know Nyssa not all MMORPG's are lvling treadmills, UO isnt.  I loved UO, and i liked EQ so i know what a mmorpg is about, its just that i guess the EQ -treadmill has wore me out.  In fact, i'm curious how many more mmorpg's will utilize the same EQ-treadmill and how long the customer base will be happy with that same system.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unyssarainwhisper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nyssa Rainwhisper</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/MiscImages/bluepawbullet.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/30/01 8:12:07 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/DAoC/lynxhead.jpg WIDTH=115 HEIGHT=116></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .......</span><hr size=1> Well Broomhilda, the lvling &quot;treadmill&quot; doesn't bore me because I don't look at it like it's work for me. I don't log on with the intentions of killing, lvling, looting, and being uber, no. I log on to enjoy the company of the friends I've made while enjoying a game. I log on, see which of my friends are on and see what they're up to and if they need help with anything. And if they're not on, and I really feel like playing, then I occupy myself by doing a trade skill or two. Otherwise I play fetch with my dogs or curl up with a good book.<br>
<br>
Sure the monotony of EQ bored me, hence why I don't like soloing or out lvling my friends. I never played UO, so I can't speak for it, but from the MMORPGs I've played (EQ, AO, DAoC), yeah, it's pretty much all about lvling unless you explore your other options, which in DAoC, in my opinion, there are plenty of options. <br>
<br>
Quite frankly, when I started playing DAoC during their final stages of beta, I didn't think much of it.  I thought it was way too much like EQ.  At the time I was completely ready to give up on MMORPGs after dealing with uber d00ds, and people bickering over loot, mobs, camps, and epics.  It put a taste in my mouth more sour than a raw lemon.  But eventually when DAoC was released, I gave it a shot, and even though I still wasn't really impressed with it, I later found out that a lot of the friends I made in EQ were moving over as well and I hooked up with them and had a blast!  As time passed, I discovered other options to the lvling routine I was so accustomed to in EQ and I can truly say I enjoy DAoC now.  Otherwise I wouldn't be paying what is it? 12 bucks a month for it?  Hell, I'd rather buy my dog an extra bag of rawhides with that money if I didn't enjoy the game.<br>
<br>
I never doubted that you know what a MMORPG is about. I'm merely saying that if you don't like a game and you're forcing yourself to log on and enjoy it, why are you playing it? You're wasting time and money when there are plenty of other things to do. I feel the frustration you must be going through just by reading your posts and honestly, I couldn't do what you're doing. I would never pay to play a game I don't enjoy. Hence why I don't play EQ anymore. Now don't get me wrong and think that I'm trying to kick you out of DAoC. I honestly don't want you to have to force yourself to like a game. No one should have to. <p><CENTER>
